# Firebase & VueFire (nuxt-vuefire)

## Firestore Data

- Use **VueFire** composables for Firestore: `useCollection`, `useDocument` (auto-imported by nuxt-vuefire)
- Get Firestore instances via `useFirebaseApp()` then `getFirestore(app)`; share collections in `app/utils/` or composables
- Prefer `useCollection` / `useDocument` for reactive, real-time Firestore data in components
- Use `useFetch` / `useAsyncData` for Nitro API routes or non-Firestore data

## Collections and references

- Use `useFirestoreCollections()` for user-scoped refs: `users/{uid}/timeBoxes`, `users/{uid}/projects`, `users/{uid}/tags`
- Use `doc(collectionRef, id)` for document references; `useDocument` returns `{ data, promise }`

## Auth

- When `vuefire.auth.enabled` is true: use `useFirebaseAuth()`, `useCurrentUser()`, `getCurrentUser()` (nuxt-vuefire composables)

## Config

- Firebase config lives in `nuxt.config.ts` under `vuefire.config`; use env vars for secrets in production
- Use Firebase MCP (`firebase_read_resources`, `firebase_init`, etc.) when setting up Firestore, rules, or auth
